text: We are No. 1 among all large states in having fully vaccinated teenagers. We are No. 2 in all large states for having fully vaccinated five- to 11- year-olds.
A U.S. law allows children as young as 11 to get vaccinated without their parents' consent.
It used to be that the only children at school who weren't vaccinated were those who had true medical conditions. Now there are 19 states that allow personal belief exemptions.
WHO says child's presence at school is enough consent for vaccination
CDC action makes the Covid-19 vaccine mandatory for schoolchildren
